The paper deals with the problem of face recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using canonical correlation analysis (CCA), which is a statistical technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experiments with a dataset, which suggests that it may fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
